1
00:00:56,241 --> 00:00:57,879
(Scrapping Wood)

2
00:00:57,880 --> 00:01:01,405
It's just a misconception, really.

3
00:01:03,530 --> 00:01:09,030
"Blind people can't truly
grasp the idea of beauty."

4
00:01:10,405 --> 00:01:15,905
No, blind folks like me...

5
00:01:17,071 --> 00:01:22,737
...we really think a lot
about what people...

6
00:01:22,738 --> 00:01:26,155
...see as beauty.

7
00:01:26,780 --> 00:01:30,196
I've spent years searching
for that beauty...

8
00:01:30,613 --> 00:01:34,239
...travelling across the country
visiting tombstones and monuments...

9
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:40,030
...touching and discovering
the beauty our ancestors left behind.

10
00:01:40,821 --> 00:01:43,279
You've been through so much.

11
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,780
Of course, of course.

12
00:01:45,405 --> 00:01:49,780
But there's something
I've been curious about.

13
00:01:49,905 --> 00:01:52,362
Your hands are remarkably delicate.

14
00:01:52,363 --> 00:01:53,697
- My hands?
- Yes.

15
00:01:53,698 --> 00:01:56,738
I expected people who engrave...

16
00:01:56,905 --> 00:01:59,529
...to have calloused hands,
but yours are so smooth...

17
00:01:59,530 --> 00:02:02,279
...do you do anything to take care of them?

18
00:02:02,636 --> 00:02:03,902
(Gasps)

19
00:02:04,825 --> 00:02:07,741
I take meticulous care of my hands.

20
00:02:08,033 --> 00:02:09,909
These hands...

21
00:02:09,910 --> 00:02:13,825
They're like my eyes...

22
00:02:14,075 --> 00:02:16,074
...you know?

23
00:02:16,075 --> 00:02:19,408
I see and feel through them.

24
00:02:19,783 --> 00:02:22,200
What about that scar?

25
00:02:22,491 --> 00:02:24,741
Oh, this?

26
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:28,033
I hurt myself when I was young...

27
00:02:28,908 --> 00:02:32,366
For us, learning a job can be hard.

28
00:02:32,991 --> 00:02:36,949
Ordinary people like us
can't even imagine...

29
00:02:36,950 --> 00:02:39,075
...how hard that must have been...

30
00:02:40,450 --> 00:02:44,450
Let's shift gears a bit.

31
00:02:45,908 --> 00:02:48,616
You're a stamp engraving artisan...

32
00:02:48,825 --> 00:02:51,034
...but also a single dad...

33
00:02:51,035 --> 00:02:54,950
...and your son now runs
CHEONGPUNG ENGRAVING.

34
00:02:55,283 --> 00:02:56,783
- Hm?
- Yes.

35
00:02:57,325 --> 00:03:01,450
I think our viewers would be curious
about that part of your life.

36
00:03:01,451 --> 00:03:03,365
Why would they be curious about that?

37
00:03:03,366 --> 00:03:05,782
Raising a child alone is hard enough...

38
00:03:05,783 --> 00:03:11,241
...let alone as someone
who's visually impaired.

39
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:14,574
Everyone tries to raise their kids well,
even in hardship.

40
00:03:14,575 --> 00:03:15,799
(Chuckles)

41
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:20,562
Kids pretty much grow up on
their own if you let them.

42
00:03:20,563 --> 00:03:24,325
Children don't grow up on their own,
you raised him!

43
00:03:24,991 --> 00:03:28,450
That's what we're curious about...

44
00:03:29,116 --> 00:03:35,116
...about your struggles
and the thoughts you had...

45
00:03:37,283 --> 00:03:39,200
It was hard.

46
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:41,658
Yes.

47
00:03:42,325 --> 00:03:44,657
What's the use of dwelling on hardships?

48
00:03:44,658 --> 00:03:45,582
(Scoffs)

49
00:03:47,783 --> 00:03:50,325
Feel free to take your time.

50
00:03:50,691 --> 00:03:51,340
(Beep Sound)

51
00:03:51,341 --> 00:03:54,208
The current time is 3:04 p.m.

52
00:03:54,866 --> 00:03:57,033
Dong-hwan, let me take a short break.

53
00:03:57,158 --> 00:03:58,575
Father, they're busy people.

54
00:03:58,576 --> 00:04:00,034
I'm sorry, one moment.

55
00:04:00,035 --> 00:04:02,034
- My apologies.
- We should continue a bit more...

56
00:04:02,035 --> 00:04:04,159
Sorry,
I didn't realize how quickly time flew.

57
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,659
- It was so fascinating.
- Sorry about that.

58
00:04:05,660 --> 00:04:07,865
Let's take a short break, I'm sorry.

59
00:04:07,866 --> 00:04:10,325
- Have a smoke, father.
- Take five, everyone!

60
00:04:10,783 --> 00:04:12,147
Here's the door.

61
00:04:12,148 --> 00:04:13,175
(Sighs)

62
00:04:15,616 --> 00:04:16,949
Commendation.

63
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:17,769
(Grunts)

64
00:04:18,746 --> 00:04:19,785
(Sighs)

65
00:04:20,265 --> 00:04:23,015
Dong-hwan, your father is truly remarkable.

66
00:04:23,207 --> 00:04:24,246
(Scoffs)

67
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:27,807
He's more than I could
ever hope to deserve.

68
00:04:28,015 --> 00:04:29,016
Just look at this!

69
00:04:29,017 --> 00:04:32,307
"I'm Yeong-gyu is proof
that miracles are real."

70
00:04:32,402 --> 00:04:33,364
(Gasps)

71
00:04:33,365 --> 00:04:35,223
What a headline.

72
00:04:37,515 --> 00:04:38,932
What's this?

73
00:04:40,015 --> 00:04:41,182
Oh, that?

74
00:04:41,183 --> 00:04:46,473
It's an old photo from when he
first opened his engraving stand.

75
00:04:47,330 --> 00:04:48,031
(Sighs)

76
00:04:48,032 --> 00:04:50,390
It's the only old photo we have.

77
00:04:51,424 --> 00:04:53,064
You look just like him.

78
00:04:53,065 --> 00:04:54,156
(Scoffs)

79
00:04:54,157 --> 00:04:55,515
Well...

80
00:04:56,140 --> 00:05:00,223
...I thought so too, so, a long time ago...

81
00:05:00,723 --> 00:05:04,224
...I told him how much I look like him.

82
00:05:04,225 --> 00:05:07,307
What did he say? Was he happy to hear it?

83
00:05:09,307 --> 00:05:11,765
He just stood quietly, thinking.

84
00:05:13,390 --> 00:05:14,973
I guess...

85
00:05:16,098 --> 00:05:20,557
...maybe he was reflecting
on the idea of resemblance...

86
00:05:21,515 --> 00:05:25,640
...since he's been blind from birth.

87
00:05:27,598 --> 00:05:29,223
That's true.

88
00:05:29,807 --> 00:05:32,307
He's never even seen his own face...

89
00:05:33,057 --> 00:05:35,390
...I never thought of it like that.

90
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,307
Where did you put the ashtray?

91
00:05:37,807 --> 00:05:39,098
Here, give it to me.

92
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:40,682
Have you rested enough, sir?

93
00:05:40,683 --> 00:05:41,433
Oh, yes, yes.

94
00:05:41,434 --> 00:05:43,516
Shall we continue?

95
00:05:43,517 --> 00:05:44,265
Sure.

96
00:05:45,348 --> 00:05:47,598
Let's continue the shoot!

97
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:50,181
- Camera.
- Coming.

98
00:05:50,182 --> 00:05:51,281
(Footstep)

99
00:05:51,282 --> 00:05:51,975
Sorry about that.

100
00:05:51,976 --> 00:05:53,182
Not at all.

101
00:05:53,183 --> 00:05:55,515
Let's get a close up of his hand.

102
00:05:57,765 --> 00:05:58,724
Good to go.

103
00:05:58,725 --> 00:06:01,057
Let's take it slow.

104
00:06:12,015 --> 00:06:24,472
<i>THE UGLY</i>

105
00:06:24,473 --> 00:06:26,279
(Liquid Pouring)

106
00:06:26,615 --> 00:06:27,514
(Thud)

107
00:06:28,779 --> 00:06:29,904
(Sighs)

108
00:06:40,425 --> 00:06:41,072
Father.

109
00:06:42,675 --> 00:06:43,218
Here.

110
00:06:43,219 --> 00:06:44,925
- Tea time already?
- Yes.

111
00:06:46,675 --> 00:06:47,467
It's hot.

112
00:06:47,468 --> 00:06:48,800
Got it.

113
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:50,383
I got it.

114
00:06:52,178 --> 00:06:53,545
(Sighs)

115
00:06:54,905 --> 00:06:57,113
Is it tough doing these interviews?

116
00:06:57,396 --> 00:06:58,295
(Sighs)

117
00:06:59,465 --> 00:07:03,345
They've been pestering me for days,
acting like this is some big deal.

118
00:07:03,665 --> 00:07:06,623
The last news segment only
took half a day to shoot.

119
00:07:06,624 --> 00:07:10,748
Just bear with it a little longer, okay?

120
00:07:11,582 --> 00:07:15,665
It's great publicity for the studio,
and it isn't easy to get on TV.

121
00:07:16,207 --> 00:07:17,915
I know...

122
00:07:18,499 --> 00:07:21,749
...if it's good for you, I guess it's fine.

123
00:07:23,207 --> 00:07:26,582
But that young producer is such a pain.

124
00:07:26,749 --> 00:07:29,041
Why does she treat me like a kid?

125
00:07:29,042 --> 00:07:31,289
Always bossing me around,
"Do this" or "Do that!"

126
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:35,428
All producers are like that,
don't let it bother you.

127
00:07:35,631 --> 00:07:36,967
(Chuckles)

128
00:07:37,363 --> 00:07:38,363
You're right.

129
00:07:39,124 --> 00:07:40,749
At my age, earning a living...

130
00:07:41,165 --> 00:07:44,457
I'm just grateful to be acknowledged.

131
00:07:45,825 --> 00:07:48,448
Do you know how jealous Gyu-chil is of me?

132
00:07:48,553 --> 00:07:49,756
(Chuckles)

133
00:07:51,117 --> 00:07:54,908
That guy's broke,
but he's constantly going on trips.

134
00:07:54,909 --> 00:07:57,493
What?
He hasn't come back from Southeast Asia?

135
00:07:57,494 --> 00:07:58,242
No.

136
00:07:58,534 --> 00:08:00,534
I'm so disappointed.

137
00:08:00,947 --> 00:08:03,655
He could've taken you with him,
why'd he go alone?

138
00:08:03,909 --> 00:08:06,574
What for? There's nothing for me to see.

139
00:08:06,575 --> 00:08:10,500
You've been friends for decades,
travelling together would've been nice.

140
00:08:11,745 --> 00:08:13,245
He's no friend of mine.

141
00:08:13,646 --> 00:08:14,959
(Chuckles)

142
00:08:15,617 --> 00:08:17,242
Don't say things you don't really mean.

143
00:08:17,381 --> 00:08:18,008
(Lip Smack)

144
00:08:18,009 --> 00:08:20,408
Alright, I've got a call, one moment.

145
00:08:20,409 --> 00:08:21,365
Okay.

146
00:08:21,366 --> 00:08:22,815
(Phone Vibrating)

147
00:08:23,705 --> 00:08:24,326
Hello?

148
00:08:24,327 --> 00:08:26,242
Is this Mr. I'm Dong-hwan?

149
00:08:26,534 --> 00:08:27,534
Yes, who is this?

150
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:30,034
This is Namil Police Station.

151
00:08:31,025 --> 00:08:32,276
The police station?

152
00:08:32,277 --> 00:08:34,734
We're calling about Jung Young-hee.

153
00:08:35,705 --> 00:08:36,521
Who is that?

154
00:08:37,025 --> 00:08:38,523
You don't know Jung Young-hee?

155
00:08:39,425 --> 00:08:41,175
She's your mother.

156
00:08:47,783 --> 00:08:48,408
What?

157
00:09:06,467 --> 00:09:08,615
(Fabric Rustle)

158
00:09:19,497 --> 00:09:21,121
You say this is my mother?

159
00:09:21,122 --> 00:09:22,271
(Groans)

160
00:09:22,497 --> 00:09:24,580
That's what we presume.

161
00:09:24,955 --> 00:09:27,955
We found an ID card with the remains.

162
00:09:28,455 --> 00:09:32,247
The body was found while excavating
a mountain for a construction site...

163
00:09:32,334 --> 00:09:33,864
(Plastic Rustle)

164
00:09:33,865 --> 00:09:36,070
...and we found personal belongings.

165
00:09:36,538 --> 00:09:38,706
Judging by the condition of the remains...

166
00:09:38,707 --> 00:09:40,997
...it's been about 40 years.

167
00:09:41,413 --> 00:09:45,872
The state of the body makes it difficult
to determine the cause of death.

168
00:09:46,122 --> 00:09:49,122
All we know is that she
died 40 years ago...

169
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:51,161
...and was buried in the mountain.

170
00:09:51,162 --> 00:09:52,119
(Long Breath)

171
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:55,895
It's hard to say if it
was an accident or not...

172
00:09:56,645 --> 00:09:59,104
...but given how the body was buried...

173
00:09:59,545 --> 00:10:01,189
...there's a chance of foul play.

174
00:10:02,562 --> 00:10:05,937
Even so,
the statute of limitations has long expired.

175
00:10:06,279 --> 00:10:07,628
(Sighs)

176
00:10:17,854 --> 00:10:22,101
National ID: Jung Young-hee.

177
00:10:22,425 --> 00:10:26,225
<i>Funeral Home.</i>

178
00:10:29,545 --> 00:10:32,084
(Footstep)

179
00:10:32,437 --> 00:10:34,687
Don't work too hard, no one's here anyway.

180
00:10:35,107 --> 00:10:36,407
(Indistinct)

181
00:10:41,896 --> 00:10:42,769
(Indistinct Utensil Clatter)

182
00:10:42,770 --> 00:10:43,990
(Sighs)

183
00:10:44,646 --> 00:10:45,834
(Indistinct)

184
00:10:49,561 --> 00:10:50,561
Is that you?

185
00:10:50,705 --> 00:10:51,580
Yes.

186
00:10:51,955 --> 00:10:52,955
Okay.

187
00:10:53,303 --> 00:10:54,078
(Groans)

188
00:10:54,079 --> 00:10:55,729
Anyone from the association here?

189
00:10:55,854 --> 00:10:59,145
Not yet, they sent a wreath though.

190
00:11:00,943 --> 00:11:01,967
(Groans)

191
00:11:03,037 --> 00:11:04,045
(Sighs)

192
00:11:04,959 --> 00:11:05,873
(Sighs)

193
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:08,703
(Gasps)

194
00:11:08,704 --> 00:11:10,270
- Father.
- Yeah?

195
00:11:12,479 --> 00:11:14,229
Wasn't it that...

196
00:11:15,270 --> 00:11:19,520
...mother just ran away, leaving us behind?

197
00:11:20,812 --> 00:11:22,729
That's what I thought too.

198
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:29,895
I came home from work...

199
00:11:30,562 --> 00:11:32,395
...and only you were in the room...

200
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,645
...she wasn't there.

201
00:11:35,687 --> 00:11:38,520
And... that was it.

202
00:11:39,432 --> 00:11:40,151
(Lip Smack)

203
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:45,729
No one came looking for
her or anything like that?

204
00:11:46,270 --> 00:11:47,437
Not at all.

205
00:11:49,104 --> 00:11:52,895
Neither of us had any family to speak of...

206
00:11:54,104 --> 00:12:00,020
She wouldn't have had any enemies, right?

207
00:12:01,270 --> 00:12:02,520
Of course not.

208
00:12:03,345 --> 00:12:06,303
Your mother was such a kind person.

209
00:12:06,687 --> 00:12:08,062
You know...

210
00:12:09,105 --> 00:12:10,314
Why would you say that?

211
00:12:10,315 --> 00:12:11,536
It's nothing.

212
00:12:12,185 --> 00:12:14,643
It's just...

213
00:12:15,785 --> 00:12:18,409
...after 40 years,
suddenly hearing that she passed away...

214
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:20,618
...I was just curious,
don't worry about it.

215
00:12:21,112 --> 00:12:21,917
(Gasps)

216
00:12:24,801 --> 00:12:25,676
Excuse me.

217
00:12:27,678 --> 00:12:30,595
We have guests, father. The producer.

218
00:12:31,105 --> 00:12:32,105
Please come in.

219
00:12:33,265 --> 00:12:34,848
I should've prepared this.

220
00:12:36,323 --> 00:12:37,377
(Long Breath)

221
00:12:38,272 --> 00:12:38,975
(Gasps)

222
00:12:42,745 --> 00:12:46,286
For this to happen in
the middle of filming...

223
00:12:46,287 --> 00:12:48,496
...I don't know what to say.

224
00:12:48,497 --> 00:12:51,161
I'm really sorry about this.

225
00:12:51,162 --> 00:12:51,854
(Sighs)

226
00:12:52,185 --> 00:12:54,852
It seems this will disrupt the broadcast...

227
00:12:55,644 --> 00:12:56,263
...is that okay?

228
00:12:56,264 --> 00:12:58,055
We can't have disruptions.

229
00:12:58,768 --> 00:13:01,102
We'll stick with you until the end.

230
00:13:02,602 --> 00:13:03,228
Pardon?

231
00:13:03,229 --> 00:13:05,310
As I mentioned before...

232
00:13:05,477 --> 00:13:09,477
...the schedule's finalized,
and delaying it isn't an option.

233
00:13:09,977 --> 00:13:15,393
Besides, these moments might feel
more authentic to the viewers.

234
00:13:16,643 --> 00:13:17,534
(Scoffs)

235
00:13:18,752 --> 00:13:20,001
Well, but...

236
00:13:20,002 --> 00:13:20,971
(Gasps)

237
00:13:21,518 --> 00:13:24,185
I mean, it's just a bit...

238
00:13:24,768 --> 00:13:26,477
Don't worry.

239
00:13:26,727 --> 00:13:28,768
We'll handle everything.

240
00:13:29,518 --> 00:13:30,810
Alright, but...

241
00:13:31,042 --> 00:13:32,065
(Sighs)

242
00:13:33,185 --> 00:13:35,309
...my father might feel differently.

243
00:13:35,310 --> 00:13:37,018
I'm counting on you.

244
00:13:38,768 --> 00:13:40,518
This must be the place.

245
00:13:40,651 --> 00:13:42,315
(Footstep)

246
00:13:45,393 --> 00:13:48,455
Please have some. I'll be right back.

247
00:13:48,557 --> 00:13:51,307
(Footstep)

248
00:13:51,685 --> 00:13:52,643
Hello.

249
00:13:53,685 --> 00:13:54,852
May I help you?

250
00:13:55,227 --> 00:13:57,352
He must be the son.

251
00:13:58,227 --> 00:14:00,893
I'm your aunt, we're Young-hee's sisters.

252
00:14:09,549 --> 00:14:10,742
(Indistinct)

253
00:14:10,743 --> 00:14:13,075
After getting a call from the police...

254
00:14:15,102 --> 00:14:19,226
...we thought it was
the right thing to come here.

255
00:14:19,227 --> 00:14:23,517
She was my aunt, after all.

256
00:14:23,518 --> 00:14:24,810
I see.

257
00:14:25,643 --> 00:14:29,768
I also want to sincerely pay my respects.

258
00:14:29,935 --> 00:14:32,977
Thank you all for coming.

259
00:14:35,643 --> 00:14:36,635
(Sighs)

260
00:14:37,596 --> 00:14:38,901
(Slurping Liquid)

261
00:14:39,505 --> 00:14:40,839
Also...

262
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:45,005
...we came here to clarify something.

263
00:14:45,630 --> 00:14:48,298
My grandfather left a small inheritance...

264
00:14:48,299 --> 00:14:53,505
...to my mother and your mother...

265
00:14:54,214 --> 00:14:56,839
...but we're not willing to share that.

266
00:14:59,510 --> 00:15:00,424
(Scoffs)

267
00:15:00,785 --> 00:15:01,701
Pardon?

268
00:15:01,826 --> 00:15:05,159
From what my mother told me...

269
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:09,494
...your mother left home
when she was very young...

270
00:15:09,495 --> 00:15:12,785
...so, she had no interaction
with us - - I see, I see.

271
00:15:13,904 --> 00:15:16,904
I'm a bit taken aback,
but I don't need the money.

272
00:15:17,545 --> 00:15:19,003
This is all so sudden...

273
00:15:21,307 --> 00:15:22,502
(Chuckles)

274
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:28,076
Besides, discussing money at a time
like this doesn't seem right.

275
00:15:29,785 --> 00:15:30,826
You're okay with that, right?

276
00:15:32,493 --> 00:15:33,493
Okay.

277
00:15:38,285 --> 00:15:39,618
I'm sorry about that.

278
00:15:41,535 --> 00:15:44,076
I thought you'd agree to it.

279
00:15:44,368 --> 00:15:46,742
In that case,
would it be okay to record this conver -.

280
00:15:46,743 --> 00:15:47,867
Please!

281
00:15:49,401 --> 00:15:50,092
(Gasps)

282
00:15:50,093 --> 00:15:51,243
Later...

283
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:55,576
...I'll write a formal statement...

284
00:15:55,993 --> 00:15:58,451
...and get it notarized.

285
00:15:58,868 --> 00:16:00,410
I'll send it by courier.

286
00:16:01,576 --> 00:16:02,451
Good?

287
00:16:02,618 --> 00:16:03,910
Very well.

288
00:16:04,493 --> 00:16:05,785
My apologies.

289
00:16:05,971 --> 00:16:07,002
(Sighs)

290
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:09,799
(Tch)

291
00:16:10,076 --> 00:16:12,077
I don't need anything...

292
00:16:12,078 --> 00:16:16,534
...but I feel awful about holding
her funeral without a photo...

293
00:16:16,535 --> 00:16:17,768
(Gasps)

294
00:16:18,285 --> 00:16:20,160
...so, let me ask you for a favour.

295
00:16:20,161 --> 00:16:22,077
If you have a photo of her...

296
00:16:22,078 --> 00:16:24,701
...could you please share it with me?

297
00:16:26,618 --> 00:16:27,869
There aren't any.

298
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:28,993
No photos of her.

299
00:16:29,410 --> 00:16:30,201
What?

300
00:16:31,035 --> 00:16:32,201
They don't exist.

301
00:16:32,826 --> 00:16:34,701
She didn't like taking photos.

302
00:16:36,410 --> 00:16:37,910
Her face was...

303
00:16:38,118 --> 00:16:40,368
...a bit ugly...

304
00:16:42,660 --> 00:16:44,660
I guess you wouldn't know.

305
00:16:45,118 --> 00:16:46,368
Young-hee...

306
00:16:46,549 --> 00:16:47,221
(Sighs)

307
00:16:47,493 --> 00:16:49,576
...didn't like taking photos...

308
00:16:50,118 --> 00:16:53,326
...because she was ugly.

309
00:16:59,785 --> 00:17:02,785
<i>The First Interview.</i>

310
00:17:04,505 --> 00:17:05,546
Ugly?

311
00:17:07,921 --> 00:17:09,838
What do you mean by that?

312
00:17:13,255 --> 00:17:15,380
Did she have some kind of disability?

313
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:18,255
She had her shortcomings...

314
00:17:18,421 --> 00:17:21,338
...but it's not like she
was a gimp or anything.

315
00:17:22,630 --> 00:17:24,672
She was just ugly, that's all.

316
00:17:24,673 --> 00:17:27,671
Why do you keep saying that?

317
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:29,963
Seriously, even just now...

318
00:17:30,796 --> 00:17:33,380
...you said she ran
away when she was a kid.

319
00:17:33,796 --> 00:17:34,340
Yeah.

320
00:17:34,341 --> 00:17:36,546
She just ran away from home like that?

321
00:17:36,671 --> 00:17:38,795
Yeah, she just left without any warning.

322
00:17:38,796 --> 00:17:40,670
That makes sense to you?

323
00:17:40,671 --> 00:17:43,546
A little kid? Running away for no reason?

324
00:17:43,921 --> 00:17:45,297
You never suspected anything?

325
00:17:45,298 --> 00:17:47,963
She could've been kidnapped, even.

326
00:17:48,296 --> 00:17:52,171
What kind of lunatic would
kidnap a girl so ugly?

327
00:17:52,338 --> 00:17:53,963
She just up and left!

328
00:17:54,088 --> 00:17:56,296
Young-hee, she...

329
00:17:56,921 --> 00:18:00,463
...told weird stories to the neighbours.

330
00:18:00,884 --> 00:18:02,800
What kind of stories?

331
00:18:02,801 --> 00:18:03,799
(Sighs)

332
00:18:03,963 --> 00:18:06,005
She claimed...

333
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:11,296
...she saw father with another woman,
both undressed...

334
00:18:12,088 --> 00:18:14,005
...at his real estate office.

335
00:18:14,332 --> 00:18:15,104
(Sighs)

336
00:18:15,105 --> 00:18:17,838
So, mother got angry...

337
00:18:18,505 --> 00:18:21,463
...and beat her really badly.

338
00:18:22,025 --> 00:18:26,108
Afterward, she was sick for a few days...

339
00:18:27,296 --> 00:18:28,588
...then she just left.

340
00:18:29,421 --> 00:18:31,255
She didn't just leave...

341
00:18:31,380 --> 00:18:34,796
...she took all of mother's
jewellery and valuables.

342
00:18:35,255 --> 00:18:38,380
To mother,
she wasn't a daughter - she was a thief.

343
00:18:38,381 --> 00:18:39,713
That's not right.

344
00:18:42,046 --> 00:18:44,838
If a husband is cheating...

345
00:18:45,171 --> 00:18:47,505
...he's the one who should be blamed.

346
00:18:47,506 --> 00:18:49,422
Beating up a child for speaking up?

347
00:18:49,423 --> 00:18:51,214
Isn't that the mother's fault?

348
00:18:51,215 --> 00:18:53,963
We were a perfectly happy family...

349
00:18:54,255 --> 00:18:57,337
...and that freak of a girl
destroyed it with her rumours...

350
00:18:57,338 --> 00:18:59,630
...of course she should be beaten
within an inch of her life!

351
00:18:59,631 --> 00:19:01,214
Don't talk like that!

352
00:19:01,215 --> 00:19:02,546
In any case...

353
00:19:03,005 --> 00:19:06,755
...that's all we know about Young-hee.

354
00:19:07,755 --> 00:19:09,088
After that...

355
00:19:10,588 --> 00:19:12,213
...we lost contact with her.

356
00:19:12,505 --> 00:19:14,214
With all the jewellery she took...

357
00:19:14,215 --> 00:19:16,630
...she got more than her
share of inheritance.

358
00:19:17,421 --> 00:19:19,838
She was family in name only.

359
00:19:21,865 --> 00:19:24,156
We've done our part by coming here...

360
00:19:24,490 --> 00:19:26,240
...haven't we?

361
00:19:26,406 --> 00:19:27,948
That's right, Aunt.

362
00:19:28,305 --> 00:19:31,064
Should we get going, then?

363
00:19:31,065 --> 00:19:32,498
Yes, let's go.

364
00:19:33,143 --> 00:19:33,655
(Clearing Throat)

365
00:19:49,365 --> 00:19:50,615
Yes, boss.

366
00:19:50,781 --> 00:19:53,198
Sir, you've got to trust me on this one.

367
00:19:54,115 --> 00:19:58,156
I think the story of his
wife is even more compelling.

368
00:19:58,781 --> 00:20:01,198
I've got a strong feeling...

369
00:20:01,448 --> 00:20:05,115
...that we've hit on
a much bigger story here.

370
00:20:08,073 --> 00:20:09,656
I'm sure of it.

371
00:20:09,831 --> 00:20:12,164
It's an undeniably gripping story.

372
00:20:13,623 --> 00:20:17,998
Entertaining? Absolutely!

373
00:20:19,448 --> 00:20:21,990
Then I'll get to work.

374
00:20:23,448 --> 00:20:26,865
Okay, thank you, bye.

375
00:20:47,209 --> 00:20:48,560
(Thud)

376
00:20:52,698 --> 00:20:54,573
You can stand here.

377
00:20:54,962 --> 00:20:57,361
(Metal Clinking)

378
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:02,104
(Footstep)

379
00:21:08,963 --> 00:21:09,932
(Coughs)

380
00:21:11,865 --> 00:21:13,652
Well...

381
00:21:14,945 --> 00:21:18,236
...this is my first time
shrouding a skeleton...

382
00:21:19,526 --> 00:21:22,318
...but I've done my best to
piece the bones together.

383
00:21:22,901 --> 00:21:25,901
If you wish to say any final words,
please do so now.

384
00:21:29,196 --> 00:21:30,365
There isn't much...

385
00:21:30,485 --> 00:21:32,193
...Young-hee, rest in peace.

386
00:21:32,610 --> 00:21:34,069
If you two have anything to say...

387
00:21:34,070 --> 00:21:35,610
...make it quick so we can leave.

388
00:21:35,611 --> 00:21:37,360
I've got a weak stomach.

389
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,402
(Grunts)

390
00:21:47,110 --> 00:21:49,401
If there's nothing to say,
let's just end it.

391
00:21:49,693 --> 00:21:51,151
I'm feeling nauseous.

392
00:21:51,589 --> 00:21:52,721
(Thud)

393
00:21:52,722 --> 00:21:55,097
(Grunts)

394
00:21:55,628 --> 00:21:57,409
(Thud)

395
00:22:01,065 --> 00:22:02,225
(Groans)

396
00:22:03,610 --> 00:22:05,610
Seriously...

397
00:22:06,377 --> 00:22:09,127
Do you know how long it
took to put this together?

398
00:22:09,610 --> 00:22:11,776
It'll all be cremated anyway.

399
00:22:12,106 --> 00:22:13,230
But I'm sorry...

400
00:22:13,231 --> 00:22:15,022
...I can't take it any more.

401
00:22:16,443 --> 00:22:17,651
Christ...

402
00:22:18,193 --> 00:22:20,443
Father, don't worry, it's nothing.

403
00:22:22,235 --> 00:22:23,901
Are you okay?

404
00:22:27,776 --> 00:22:28,735
One moment.

405
00:22:30,094 --> 00:22:33,551
- Father, I need to take a call.
- Sure, sure.

406
00:22:33,552 --> 00:22:34,777
(Cane Tapping)

407
00:22:34,987 --> 00:22:38,854
(Footstep)

408
00:22:39,193 --> 00:22:40,069
Hello, Producer Kim.

409
00:22:40,070 --> 00:22:42,068
Hello? So...

410
00:22:42,693 --> 00:22:47,235
You know the commercial building
where your parents first met?

411
00:22:47,401 --> 00:22:48,275
Pardon?

412
00:22:48,276 --> 00:22:52,860
The one in the photo,
in front of the stamp stand.

413
00:22:54,705 --> 00:22:55,796
Yes, what about it?

414
00:22:56,225 --> 00:22:58,724
I asked around and found out...

415
00:22:58,725 --> 00:23:03,860
...she worked at a factory in that
building called CHEONGPUNG GARMENTS.

416
00:23:05,865 --> 00:23:08,739
CHEONGPUNG GARMENTS?

417
00:23:08,740 --> 00:23:09,985
Yes, yes.

418
00:23:10,318 --> 00:23:13,443
CHEONGPUNG ENGRAVING, CHEONGPUNG GARMENTS.

419
00:23:14,568 --> 00:23:15,985
Isn't that interesting?

420
00:23:16,568 --> 00:23:20,150
Yes, I guess...

421
00:23:20,151 --> 00:23:20,874
(Gasps)

422
00:23:20,875 --> 00:23:25,775
I got in touch with a few
factory workers from back then.

423
00:23:25,776 --> 00:23:28,568
They said they knew your mother.

424
00:23:29,193 --> 00:23:30,069
So...

425
00:23:30,070 --> 00:23:33,401
...if you're free tomorrow...

426
00:23:33,402 --> 00:23:37,193
...how about joining us
for a chat with them?

427
00:23:49,235 --> 00:23:49,903
Is that good?

428
00:23:49,904 --> 00:23:50,985
Like this?

429
00:23:51,292 --> 00:23:52,745
(Clatter)

430
00:23:54,443 --> 00:23:55,443
Let me see.

431
00:23:59,589 --> 00:24:01,213
(Birds Chirping)

432
00:24:03,505 --> 00:24:04,838
Stay in the van.

433
00:24:04,839 --> 00:24:06,550
(Footstep)

434
00:24:06,728 --> 00:24:07,936
Good to see you.

435
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:10,399
(Car Door Closes In Distant)

436
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:11,850
Ms. Kim...

437
00:24:12,667 --> 00:24:14,750
...I appreciate the gesture, but...

438
00:24:14,984 --> 00:24:16,319
Don't mention it!

439
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:18,651
No, that's not what I'm saying.

440
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,027
You don't have to go this far.

441
00:24:22,028 --> 00:24:23,111
No, no.

442
00:24:23,225 --> 00:24:27,767
I'm a journalist at heart,
digging into a story is so much fun.

443
00:24:28,081 --> 00:24:31,290
Let's go in! The elders are waiting.

444
00:24:31,401 --> 00:24:33,651
Okay? Come on.

445
00:24:37,235 --> 00:24:40,150
<i>The Second Interview.</i>

446
00:24:40,151 --> 00:24:41,542
(Door Opens)

447
00:24:42,964 --> 00:24:44,479
(Indistinct Chatter)

448
00:24:44,705 --> 00:24:46,288
Good afternoon.

449
00:24:47,145 --> 00:24:48,062
Hi.

450
00:24:48,705 --> 00:24:49,621
Have a seat.

451
00:24:49,622 --> 00:24:50,598
(Indistinct)

452
00:24:52,786 --> 00:24:53,848
(Thud)

453
00:24:54,905 --> 00:24:56,281
What can I get you two?

454
00:24:56,282 --> 00:24:57,955
Anything will be fine.

455
00:24:58,122 --> 00:24:59,871
Juice would be great.

456
00:24:59,872 --> 00:25:01,413
Very well.

457
00:25:04,865 --> 00:25:06,449
I'm Kim Su-jin...

458
00:25:06,450 --> 00:25:09,032
...the producer who contacted you.

459
00:25:10,490 --> 00:25:11,490
Here.

460
00:25:12,490 --> 00:25:14,490
And who's he?

461
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,240
This is, uh...

462
00:25:19,065 --> 00:25:20,190
I'm the writer.

463
00:25:20,699 --> 00:25:23,065
- A writer?
- Is that so?

464
00:25:23,625 --> 00:25:25,000
Yes, our writer.

465
00:25:25,385 --> 00:25:28,510
So, you're a TV producer?

466
00:25:29,074 --> 00:25:30,824
Is this for the news?

467
00:25:30,990 --> 00:25:32,740
Yes, something like that.

468
00:25:32,907 --> 00:25:37,824
We're investigating the story
of Ms. Jung Young-hee.

469
00:25:38,740 --> 00:25:41,574
Her remains were discovered...

470
00:25:41,782 --> 00:25:45,990
...near the garment factory
where you all used to work.

471
00:25:46,115 --> 00:25:48,740
It seems she died about 40 years ago.

472
00:25:49,282 --> 00:25:50,115
Oh dear...

473
00:25:50,324 --> 00:25:51,408
When you called...

474
00:25:51,409 --> 00:25:54,824
...we assumed she died some place far away.

475
00:25:54,981 --> 00:25:56,043
(Gasps)

476
00:25:56,133 --> 00:26:00,716
Back then she just vanished,
so we thought she'd run away.

477
00:26:02,024 --> 00:26:04,418
Seems she met some terrible misfortune.

478
00:26:04,629 --> 00:26:05,173
(Tch)

479
00:26:05,174 --> 00:26:06,324
Oh dear...

480
00:26:07,074 --> 00:26:10,782
She just stopped coming
to the factory one day?

481
00:26:11,324 --> 00:26:14,949
Yes, so we thought she had run away.

482
00:26:16,028 --> 00:26:16,778
(Glass Clinking)

483
00:26:17,074 --> 00:26:18,265
Was there...

484
00:26:19,665 --> 00:26:22,457
...anyone at the factory...

485
00:26:22,615 --> 00:26:26,449
...who was close to her by any chance?

486
00:26:26,949 --> 00:26:28,365
Well...

487
00:26:29,425 --> 00:26:31,966
...the only person close to Dung Ogre...

488
00:26:32,425 --> 00:26:37,050
...was the blind guy who
ended up marrying her.

489
00:26:37,825 --> 00:26:39,242
"Dung Ogre"?

490
00:26:39,621 --> 00:26:40,413
That's...

491
00:26:40,414 --> 00:26:42,581
We called her "Dung Ogre"...

492
00:26:42,784 --> 00:26:45,233
...because of her face and all.

493
00:26:45,234 --> 00:26:46,758
(Chuckles)

494
00:26:46,759 --> 00:26:48,616
Come on now.

495
00:26:48,617 --> 00:26:49,247
(Click)

496
00:26:49,367 --> 00:26:52,325
No one literally looks like dung...

497
00:26:53,117 --> 00:26:57,367
...but there was a reason
behind the nickname.

498
00:26:57,458 --> 00:26:58,589
(Chuckles)

499
00:26:58,590 --> 00:27:00,325
What reason was that?

500
00:27:01,434 --> 00:27:02,824
(Chuckles)

501
00:27:02,825 --> 00:27:04,117
I can't...

502
00:27:04,784 --> 00:27:07,450
Come on, you can tell me.

503
00:27:07,778 --> 00:27:08,879
It's all in the past.

504
00:27:10,585 --> 00:27:11,794
Back then...

505
00:27:11,795 --> 00:27:14,293
...everything was so hectic.

506
00:27:15,425 --> 00:27:17,716
It was a real boom period.

507
00:27:17,901 --> 00:27:21,484
We were so busy, every day was a whirlwind.

508
00:27:21,575 --> 00:27:22,928
(Indistinct Chatter)

509
00:27:22,929 --> 00:27:27,413
The country was literally on the rise.

510
00:27:33,028 --> 00:27:35,450
(Indistinct Chatter)

511
00:27:45,637 --> 00:27:47,762
(Indistinct Chatter)

512
00:28:08,793 --> 00:28:10,850
(Indistinct Chatter)

513
00:28:10,851 --> 00:28:13,001
<i>CHEONGPUNG GARMENTS</i>

514
00:28:15,625 --> 00:28:18,041
Young-hee! What took you so long?!

515
00:28:18,402 --> 00:28:21,569
Hurry up and bring the fabric!
Move your ass, will you!

516
00:28:21,973 --> 00:28:23,637
(Sewing Machine Whirring)

517
00:28:25,817 --> 00:28:28,075
(Indistinct Chatter)

518
00:28:30,645 --> 00:28:33,247
(Iron Steaming)

519
00:28:33,684 --> 00:28:35,819
(Indistinct Chatter)

520
00:28:40,105 --> 00:28:43,813
Hey, I told you to clear this away.

521
00:28:44,710 --> 00:28:47,126
You've been messing with this all day!

522
00:28:48,645 --> 00:28:49,863
(Gasps)

523
00:28:50,543 --> 00:28:53,376
Excuse me, boss...

524
00:28:54,305 --> 00:28:56,055
I'm sorry, but...

525
00:28:57,013 --> 00:28:58,971
...could I use the bathroom...?

526
00:28:59,430 --> 00:29:02,013
We're drowning in work, there's no time!

527
00:29:02,014 --> 00:29:03,805
I-I'm sorry...

528
00:29:04,481 --> 00:29:05,808
(Whimpering)

529
00:29:05,809 --> 00:29:07,805
It's urgent...

530
00:29:08,905 --> 00:29:10,312
Get back here in one minute.

531
00:29:10,535 --> 00:29:11,755
Thank you.

532
00:29:12,950 --> 00:29:15,145
(Panting)

533
00:29:21,208 --> 00:29:23,168
(Groans)

534
00:29:27,471 --> 00:29:29,331
<i>Toilet.</i>

535
00:29:31,168 --> 00:29:33,692
(Groans)

536
00:29:36,848 --> 00:29:37,756
(Pants)

537
00:29:43,197 --> 00:29:44,778
(Groans)

538
00:29:48,707 --> 00:29:51,629
(Chuckles)

539
00:29:51,721 --> 00:29:56,638
She took his words literally,
and had no time to poop.

540
00:29:57,263 --> 00:30:00,554
She stupidly ended up going in her pants.

541
00:30:00,555 --> 00:30:01,417
(Chuckles)

542
00:30:08,096 --> 00:30:10,055
Clean it up now!

543
00:30:13,930 --> 00:30:17,471
It was such a strange and pitiful sight.

544
00:30:17,905 --> 00:30:19,988
Her face was bad enough...

545
00:30:20,665 --> 00:30:23,625
...but then to poop her pants...

546
00:30:24,221 --> 00:30:28,055
Everyone called her "Dung Ogre" after that.

547
00:30:33,763 --> 00:30:38,222
What exactly did she look like...

548
00:30:38,223 --> 00:30:41,264
...for people to talk about
her appearance so much?

549
00:30:41,785 --> 00:30:46,035
Did she have a facial deformity
or something like that?

550
00:30:46,036 --> 00:30:47,326
A deformity?

551
