01:03:59,329 --> 01:04:01,287
Is anyone there?!

1105
01:04:03,265 --> 01:04:04,974
Help!

1106
01:04:05,585 --> 01:04:06,431
Please help...

1107
01:04:07,430 --> 01:04:08,734
(Sobbing)

1108
01:04:17,445 --> 01:04:19,945
(Humming)

1109
01:04:20,095 --> 01:04:22,625
(Water Tinkles)

1110
01:04:22,626 --> 01:04:23,719
(Paper Rustle)

1111
01:04:28,383 --> 01:04:30,258
(Muttering)

1112
01:04:32,180 --> 01:04:33,430
(Door Opens)

1113
01:04:33,711 --> 01:04:35,577
(Grunts)

1114
01:04:35,578 --> 01:04:36,799
(Thud)

1115
01:04:36,800 --> 01:04:38,575
What the hell are you doing?! You lunatic!

1116
01:04:38,867 --> 01:04:41,575
What did I do wrong? Tell me!

1117
01:04:41,680 --> 01:04:42,424
(Grunts)

1118
01:04:42,425 --> 01:04:43,368
Holy shit.

1119
01:04:43,369 --> 01:04:44,825
Anyone outside?!

1120
01:04:44,826 --> 01:04:47,034
- What did I do wrong?!
- Anyone outside?!

1121
01:04:47,325 --> 01:04:48,368
Get her off me!

1122
01:04:48,369 --> 01:04:49,492
Dammit...

1123
01:04:50,078 --> 01:04:51,562
(Screams)

1124
01:04:51,976 --> 01:04:53,414
(Pants)

1125
01:04:53,909 --> 01:04:55,409
That psychotic bitch.

1126
01:04:55,617 --> 01:04:57,203
(Pants)

1127
01:04:57,562 --> 01:05:00,695
(Sobbing)

1128
01:05:00,953 --> 01:05:02,962
(Whimpering)

1129
01:05:03,766 --> 01:05:04,516
(Gasps)

1130
01:05:05,075 --> 01:05:09,159
It looked like those idiots...

1131
01:05:10,034 --> 01:05:14,833
...botched the job, so I sent them back.

1132
01:05:16,745 --> 01:05:22,286
I said to make it so she
couldn't get up for a few days.

1133
01:05:23,398 --> 01:05:25,711
(Crickets Chirping)

1134
01:05:25,820 --> 01:05:29,280
(Footsteps)

1135
01:05:33,867 --> 01:05:40,784
They said the blind gimp came out.

1136
01:05:41,650 --> 01:05:43,390
(Crickets Chirping)

1137
01:05:43,703 --> 01:05:45,766
(Footsteps)

1138
01:05:46,000 --> 01:05:48,836
(Cane Tapping)

1139
01:05:56,219 --> 01:05:58,344
(Footstep)

1140
01:06:03,804 --> 01:06:08,820
(Footstep)

1141
01:06:08,992 --> 01:06:10,742
Isn't that weird?

1142
01:06:11,208 --> 01:06:14,500
There was no need to kill her.

1143
01:06:14,891 --> 01:06:16,882
(Pants)

1144
01:06:19,016 --> 01:06:22,218
(Crickets Chirping)

1145
01:06:24,566 --> 01:06:25,545
(Gasps)

1146
01:06:29,914 --> 01:06:30,628
(Grunts)

1147
01:06:30,629 --> 01:06:34,971
(Thuds)

1148
01:06:36,601 --> 01:06:39,851
(Pants)

1149
01:06:53,219 --> 01:06:54,578
(Gasps)

1150
01:06:54,750 --> 01:06:57,906
(Grunts)

1151
01:06:58,726 --> 01:06:59,844
(Gasps)

1152
01:07:00,836 --> 01:07:02,960
(Whimpering)

1153
01:07:03,218 --> 01:07:06,850
No one saw anything, no one saw anything...

1154
01:07:07,114 --> 01:07:08,364
Get it together...

1155
01:07:09,266 --> 01:07:12,453
(Crickets Chirping)

1156
01:07:13,505 --> 01:07:15,755
That gimp...

1157
01:07:16,422 --> 01:07:20,422
...couldn't even get rid
of the body properly...

1158
01:07:20,922 --> 01:07:24,754
...so my guys took care of it...

1159
01:07:24,755 --> 01:07:29,130
...and even held a funeral for her.

1160
01:07:29,242 --> 01:07:31,854
(Sobbing)

1161
01:07:31,855 --> 01:07:36,130
I guess they did it so
they wouldn't get blamed.

1162
01:07:36,312 --> 01:07:38,765
(Sobbing)

1163
01:07:39,031 --> 01:07:40,038
(Groans)

1164
01:07:40,039 --> 01:07:41,367
(Gasps)

1165
01:07:41,638 --> 01:07:47,096
They probably buried her so deep...

1166
01:07:47,838 --> 01:07:53,672
...that the gimp never
got caught for the murder.

1167
01:07:54,625 --> 01:07:56,385
(Sobbing)

1168
01:07:56,386 --> 01:07:58,007
(Grunts)

1169
01:08:00,601 --> 01:08:02,695
(Gasps)

1170
01:08:03,380 --> 01:08:11,422
He should be thanking us.

1171
01:08:11,547 --> 01:08:16,005
No way. Don't lie...

1172
01:08:17,880 --> 01:08:19,213
Don't lie to me.

1173
01:08:19,343 --> 01:08:20,651
(Grunts)

1174
01:08:20,755 --> 01:08:22,922
Dong-hwan, stop it, please, don't!

1175
01:08:22,923 --> 01:08:25,463
Tell me the truth.
You killed her, didn't you?!

1176
01:08:26,130 --> 01:08:28,005
Don't do this!

1177
01:08:28,255 --> 01:08:29,964
You perverted bastard!

1178
01:08:29,965 --> 01:08:30,922
Stop it!

1179
01:08:30,923 --> 01:08:32,505
You killed her.

1180
01:08:32,838 --> 01:08:35,338
You killed her, it was you!

1181
01:08:35,508 --> 01:08:36,562
(Groans)

1182
01:08:36,945 --> 01:08:38,736
This isn't the way to solve things!

1183
01:08:38,737 --> 01:08:40,278
"This isn't the way"?

1184
01:08:42,617 --> 01:08:43,508
(Slaps)

1185
01:08:43,820 --> 01:08:45,133
(Gasps)

1186
01:08:45,612 --> 01:08:46,586
Seriously?

1187
01:08:46,976 --> 01:08:49,203
(Pants)

1188
01:08:49,516 --> 01:08:50,383
(Thud)

1189
01:08:51,430 --> 01:08:54,570
(Grunts)

1190
01:08:56,412 --> 01:08:57,367
(Click)

1191
01:09:08,999 --> 01:09:09,885
(Door Opens)

1192
01:09:09,886 --> 01:09:10,810
(Door Closes)

1193
01:09:12,625 --> 01:09:13,641
(Grunts)

1194
01:09:34,945 --> 01:09:37,945
<i>The Fifth Interview.</i>

1195
01:09:45,906 --> 01:09:46,922
(Door Closes)

1196
01:09:48,125 --> 01:09:50,260
(Door Slides Open)

1197
01:09:50,261 --> 01:09:51,250
(Thud)

1198
01:09:57,336 --> 01:09:58,546
(Thud)

1199
01:10:00,180 --> 01:10:00,956
(Thud)

1200
01:10:00,957 --> 01:10:01,970
(Sighs)

1201
01:10:05,883 --> 01:10:06,953
(Light Switch quicks.)

1202
01:10:11,625 --> 01:10:14,625
Didn't know you were home. So quiet.

1203
01:10:17,208 --> 01:10:19,375
What have you been doing lately?

1204
01:10:21,791 --> 01:10:23,625
Go get some sleep.

1205
01:10:25,865 --> 01:10:26,698
Father.

1206
01:10:27,198 --> 01:10:28,114
Yeah?

1207
01:10:30,958 --> 01:10:33,958
I met a man named Baek Joo-sang today.

1208
01:10:38,166 --> 01:10:39,166
Who?

1209
01:10:40,718 --> 01:10:41,382
(Lip Smack)

1210
01:10:41,583 --> 01:10:45,375
He told me something really weird...

1211
01:10:50,425 --> 01:10:52,258
Did you kill mother?

1212
01:11:18,945 --> 01:11:19,785
But, father...

1213
01:11:23,625 --> 01:11:24,785
Why did you do it?

1214
01:11:28,272 --> 01:11:29,123
Why?

1215
01:11:35,945 --> 01:11:38,778
Back then, life was really tough.

1216
01:11:41,745 --> 01:11:43,304
Ever since I was a kid...

1217
01:11:43,912 --> 01:11:46,204
...all I remember is being
teased and beaten up.

1218
01:11:46,579 --> 01:11:47,785
Because I couldn't see...

1219
01:11:50,245 --> 01:11:52,829
When I wanted to learn
how to engrave stamps...

1220
01:11:53,180 --> 01:11:53,930
(Gasps)

1221
01:11:56,495 --> 01:11:59,620
...I was beaten for no reason.

1222
01:12:01,162 --> 01:12:03,787
It was just... complete hell.

1223
01:12:04,746 --> 01:12:11,871
But I scraped and saved by not eating,
not spending...

1224
01:12:13,452 --> 01:12:14,505
...and managed to...

1225
01:12:17,563 --> 01:12:18,985
...open a little stand.

1226
01:12:20,016 --> 01:12:21,383
(Gasps)

1227
01:12:22,162 --> 01:12:24,329
<i>Stamp Engraving</i>

1228
01:12:24,454 --> 01:12:25,465
I thought.

1229
01:12:27,370 --> 01:12:31,287
I could endure ten times
the hardship I'd already faced.

1230
01:12:33,787 --> 01:12:37,662
Come on, give me a big smile!

1231
01:12:38,220 --> 01:12:41,137
Why do you want a photo of
someone who can't even see?

1232
01:12:41,454 --> 01:12:43,080
You look great when you smile.

1233
01:12:43,207 --> 01:12:44,416
Come on, smile!

1234
01:12:45,037 --> 01:12:46,413
One-- Look this way?

1235
01:12:46,414 --> 01:12:47,704
Yeah, that's good.

1236
01:12:48,079 --> 01:12:49,203
Alright, one...

1237
01:12:49,204 --> 01:12:50,079
...two...

1238
01:12:50,329 --> 01:12:51,204
...three!

1239
01:12:51,954 --> 01:12:53,036
Very nice.

1240
01:12:53,037 --> 01:12:55,517
(Chuckles)

1241
01:12:55,961 --> 01:12:56,789
(Soft Thud)

1242
01:12:56,921 --> 01:13:03,065
It's so impressive,
doing this even though you can't see.

1243
01:13:04,665 --> 01:13:05,505
Hey.

1244
01:13:06,942 --> 01:13:10,275
When I see someone like
you working so hard...

1245
01:13:10,905 --> 01:13:13,145
...it's amazing, I really respect that.

1246
01:13:14,704 --> 01:13:22,245
Listen, I'll frame this photo
as a grand opening gift.

1247
01:13:22,534 --> 01:13:25,159
Hang it in the best spot
when you make it big, got it?

1248
01:13:28,185 --> 01:13:29,025
- Sir?
- Yeah?

1249
01:13:30,185 --> 01:13:31,185
I, uh...

1250
01:13:32,265 --> 01:13:33,181
Thank you.

1251
01:13:33,182 --> 01:13:34,011
(Chuckles)

1252
01:13:34,012 --> 01:13:35,286
- I'll work hard.
- Good.

1253
01:13:35,287 --> 01:13:36,386
(Chuckles)

1254
01:13:36,387 --> 01:13:38,954
- Yeah, work hard!
- Yes, sir!

1255
01:13:39,080 --> 01:13:40,787
- Make it big.
- Thank you!

1256
01:13:40,788 --> 01:13:43,162
- Good, I gotta go.
- Yes, sir!

1257
01:13:43,305 --> 01:13:44,414
(Chuckles)

1258
01:13:45,037 --> 01:13:46,662
- Take care, boss.
- Bye.

1259
01:13:47,013 --> 01:13:47,726
(Soft Thud)

1260
01:13:47,829 --> 01:13:48,787
Oh man...

1261
01:13:49,031 --> 01:13:50,125
(Sighs)

1262
01:13:51,805 --> 01:13:53,617
(Indistinct Chatter)

1263
01:13:56,785 --> 01:13:58,545
But things didn't go as planned.

1264
01:13:59,484 --> 01:14:00,469
(Sobbing)

1265
01:14:03,065 --> 01:14:06,024
No one cared about a blind
guy engraving stamps.

1266
01:14:07,505 --> 01:14:09,130
All I got was curious onlookers...

1267
01:14:09,131 --> 01:14:11,921
...or people picking fights
to see if I could do it.

1268
01:14:20,105 --> 01:14:21,939
That's when I met your mom.

1269
01:14:26,726 --> 01:14:27,578
(Sighs)

1270
01:14:30,273 --> 01:14:31,838
The lettering...

1271
01:14:32,505 --> 01:14:34,171
...is so pretty...

1272
01:14:35,463 --> 01:14:36,463
It's pretty?

1273
01:14:36,590 --> 01:14:38,043
(Scoffs)

1274
01:14:38,505 --> 01:14:41,838
Then would you like a stamp?

1275
01:14:42,025 --> 01:14:43,192
No...

1276
01:14:44,921 --> 01:14:46,838
I would love to...

1277
01:14:47,338 --> 01:14:53,421
But I don't have any use
for a stamp right now.

1278
01:14:54,088 --> 01:14:58,504
Maybe later... later, I'd love one.

1279
01:14:58,505 --> 01:14:59,838
No, it's okay.

1280
01:15:00,255 --> 01:15:01,755
How about this?

1281
01:15:02,671 --> 01:15:05,088
You're my very first customer...

1282
01:15:05,463 --> 01:15:08,546
...after opening this stand...

1283
01:15:10,963 --> 01:15:14,587
...how about I make one for free?

1284
01:15:14,588 --> 01:15:15,344
(Gasps)

1285
01:15:15,533 --> 01:15:16,741
Really?

1286
01:15:16,742 --> 01:15:18,033
Of course.

1287
01:15:18,273 --> 01:15:19,312
(Chuckles)

1288
01:15:20,463 --> 01:15:21,421
Let's see.

1289
01:15:22,470 --> 01:15:25,398
Give me your name.

1290
01:15:26,130 --> 01:15:28,170
It's Young-hee.

1291
01:15:28,171 --> 01:15:29,505
Young-hee.

1292
01:15:29,671 --> 01:15:31,504
Jung Young-hee.

1293
01:15:31,505 --> 01:15:33,162
Ms. Jung Young-hee.

1294
01:15:33,163 --> 01:15:35,397
That's when I learned her name.

1295
01:15:36,338 --> 01:15:38,338
Jung Young-hee.

1296
01:15:42,171 --> 01:15:43,088
Such a beautiful name.

1297
01:15:43,213 --> 01:15:45,629
You have such a beautiful name.

1298
01:15:45,630 --> 01:15:46,601
(Chuckles)

1299
01:15:46,766 --> 01:15:47,469
(Thud)

1300
01:15:47,838 --> 01:15:51,921
Since you're my first customer,
I'll make it extra special.

1301
01:15:55,465 --> 01:15:56,515
Alright.

1302
01:15:58,007 --> 01:16:01,716
Do you work at the factory here?

1303
01:16:01,838 --> 01:16:03,880
Yes.

1304
01:16:08,046 --> 01:16:10,213
Let's see... Alright.

1305
01:16:12,046 --> 01:16:14,963
Now, press it yourself.

1306
01:16:17,088 --> 01:16:18,338
Right here.

1307
01:16:20,463 --> 01:16:25,005
Dip it in the inkpad, then press it down.

1308
01:16:27,921 --> 01:16:30,295
Move it up and down...

1309
01:16:30,296 --> 01:16:32,171
...and side to side.

1310
01:16:33,585 --> 01:16:34,705
Good.

1311
01:16:34,825 --> 01:16:37,616
<i>Jung Young-hee.</i>

1312
01:16:38,190 --> 01:16:38,933
How is it?

1313
01:16:40,185 --> 01:16:42,435
It's... so pretty.

1314
01:16:42,945 --> 01:16:43,771
Is it?

1315
01:16:44,585 --> 01:16:47,945
Take this paper too.

1316
01:16:49,296 --> 01:16:51,046
Don't forget to spread the word.

1317
01:16:51,712 --> 01:16:52,488
Yes.

1318
01:16:55,825 --> 01:16:56,909
After that day...

1319
01:16:58,259 --> 01:17:00,225
...she'd stop by, chat with me...

1320
01:17:01,705 --> 01:17:04,465
...and bring me rice balls and snacks.

1321
01:17:05,588 --> 01:17:08,185
You haven't eaten lunch, right?

1322
01:17:08,671 --> 01:17:10,945
I made some extras...

1323
01:17:12,539 --> 01:17:13,625
(Indistinct Chatter)

1324
01:17:13,626 --> 01:17:15,401
What's this?

1325
01:17:15,692 --> 01:17:17,109
Just some rice balls.

1326
01:17:18,609 --> 01:17:20,276
You didn't have to...

1327
01:17:21,317 --> 01:17:22,901
For the first time in my life...

1328
01:17:23,067 --> 01:17:26,109
...someone had taken an interest in me.

1329
01:17:27,359 --> 01:17:33,317
Just hearing Young-hee's
voice made my heart race.

1330
01:17:33,609 --> 01:17:34,984
Thump-thump.

1331
01:17:35,109 --> 01:17:36,651
- Thank you.
- Sure.

1332
01:17:38,984 --> 01:17:40,734
- Thanks again!
- Okay...

1333
01:17:43,105 --> 01:17:45,645
I'm so jealous, Yeong-gyu.

1334
01:17:45,646 --> 01:17:47,901
Look at that pretty girl hitting on you.

1335
01:17:48,100 --> 01:17:49,434
I know, eh?

1336
01:17:49,777 --> 01:17:54,402
It must kill you not to
see such a stunning beauty.

1337
01:17:54,680 --> 01:17:57,680
You'd better snatch her up
before someone else does.

1338
01:17:58,109 --> 01:17:59,276
Ask her to live with you!

1339
01:17:59,277 --> 01:18:01,567
Don't let her slip away and regret it.

1340
01:18:03,570 --> 01:18:04,773
(Chuckles)

1341
01:18:05,025 --> 01:18:05,936
So lucky.

1342
01:18:07,648 --> 01:18:09,039
(Indistinct Chatter)

1343
01:18:11,151 --> 01:18:17,067
Hearing that made me anxious,
and I got scared.

1344
01:18:18,901 --> 01:18:23,442
Somehow I worked up the courage
to ask her to live with me.

1345
01:18:24,705 --> 01:18:26,105
I promised to take care of her.

1346
01:18:28,047 --> 01:18:29,539
(Sobbing)

1347
01:18:30,653 --> 01:18:35,362
And your mom said yes.

1348
01:18:35,867 --> 01:18:37,859
(Sobbing)

1349
01:18:40,672 --> 01:18:41,976
(Groans)

1350
01:18:42,705 --> 01:18:46,913
I really couldn't believe my luck.

1351
01:18:48,413 --> 01:18:51,038
Come, give them a round of applause!

1352
01:18:51,664 --> 01:18:53,718
(Crowd Cheering)

1353
01:18:56,734 --> 01:18:57,887
(Claps)

1354
01:18:57,888 --> 01:19:02,288
What's the virtue of married life?

1355
01:19:02,497 --> 01:19:04,080
Having lots of kids, right?

1356
01:19:04,372 --> 01:19:06,537
Look at this guy grinning!

1357
01:19:06,538 --> 01:19:07,971
(Laughs)

1358
01:19:07,972 --> 01:19:09,070
When does that happen, huh?

1359
01:19:09,071 --> 01:19:10,528
- At night!
- Night, night.

1360
01:19:10,529 --> 01:19:13,252
Hey, Yeong-gyu, you're so lucky.

1361
01:19:13,625 --> 01:19:14,784
It's always night for you!

1362
01:19:14,785 --> 01:19:17,428
(Laughs)

1363
01:19:17,429 --> 01:19:18,804
(Laughing And Clapping)

1364
01:19:18,805 --> 01:19:22,831
Since it's your wedding,
let me take a photo for you.

1365
01:19:22,832 --> 01:19:25,038
- Stand up straight.
- Good, good.

1366
01:19:25,039 --> 01:19:26,164
Where should I look?

1367
01:19:26,165 --> 01:19:27,912
Yeong-gyu, look this way.

1368
01:19:27,913 --> 01:19:29,054
(Claps)

1369
01:19:29,055 --> 01:19:30,456
Here we go, one...

1370
01:19:30,457 --> 01:19:33,746
That's when I formed my first real dream.

1371
01:19:33,747 --> 01:19:35,096
(Indistinct)

1372
01:19:35,097 --> 01:19:39,829
To make sure Young-hee would
never be disrespected...

1373
01:19:39,830 --> 01:19:41,140
(Indistinct)

1374
01:19:41,141 --> 01:19:43,538
...and could live an honourable life.

1375
01:19:44,133 --> 01:19:47,711
(Baby Crying)

1376
01:19:49,038 --> 01:19:51,288
Are you hungry?

1377
01:19:52,219 --> 01:19:54,609
(Baby Crying)

1378
01:19:55,172 --> 01:19:57,031
(Baby Crying)

1379
01:19:57,225 --> 01:19:58,663
I'm back.

1380
01:19:58,664 --> 01:20:00,955
Dong-hwan must be very hungry.

1381
01:20:04,538 --> 01:20:05,372
Here.

1382
01:20:08,413 --> 01:20:09,913
After having you...

1383
01:20:10,743 --> 01:20:14,660
...we barely scraped by even
with both of us working.

1384
01:20:18,163 --> 01:20:20,122
It wasn't bad though...

1385
01:20:21,385 --> 01:20:22,448
...it wasn't bad at all.

1386
01:20:28,625 --> 01:20:29,830
Then one night...

1387
01:20:31,745 --> 01:20:37,453
...Gyu-chil was in the area
for work and stopped by.

1388
01:20:43,955 --> 01:20:45,788
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Sure.

1389
01:20:49,825 --> 01:20:51,410
Here, have some of this.

1390
01:20:51,512 --> 01:20:52,428
Okay.

1391
01:20:53,546 --> 01:20:54,061
(Clatter)

1392
01:20:54,062 --> 01:20:55,172
(Chuckles)

1393
01:20:55,706 --> 01:20:58,289
She's got a good heart?

1394
01:20:58,290 --> 01:21:00,006
Yes, of course.

1395
01:21:00,484 --> 01:21:01,641
(Chuckles)

1396
01:21:02,165 --> 01:21:07,550
A blind guy like me meeting
a woman with such a kind heart...

1397
01:21:07,551 --> 01:21:09,101
(Chuckles)

1398
01:21:09,280 --> 01:21:10,637
...it's a blessing, it sure is!

1399
01:21:10,820 --> 01:21:11,725
(Chuckles)

1400
01:21:11,726 --> 01:21:12,930
(Gasps)

1401
01:21:13,226 --> 01:21:14,234
(Sighs)

1402
01:21:15,153 --> 01:21:17,987
My only regret is that
I'll never see her face...

1403
01:21:19,331 --> 01:21:20,498
...with my own eyes.

1404
01:21:20,961 --> 01:21:21,711
(Lip Smack)

1405
01:21:22,081 --> 01:21:25,123
Having a good heart is all that matters.

1406
01:21:25,484 --> 01:21:26,516
(Utensil Clinking)

1407
01:21:26,706 --> 01:21:30,040
Maybe it's better you never see her face.

1408
01:21:30,211 --> 01:21:31,226
(Soft Thud)

1409
01:21:31,415 --> 01:21:33,415
You son of a bitch...

1410
01:21:33,915 --> 01:21:40,165
My only wish is to see her face just once.

1411
01:21:40,623 --> 01:21:42,206
Don't talk shit to me.

1412
01:21:42,790 --> 01:21:44,248
No, really.

1413
01:21:44,831 --> 01:21:46,956
You're better off not seeing her.

1414
01:21:48,266 --> 01:21:49,305
(Soft Thud)

1415
01:21:49,306 --> 01:21:51,040
What are you saying?

1416
01:21:52,711 --> 01:21:53,578
(Soft Thud)

1417
01:21:54,081 --> 01:21:56,040
Has no one said anything to you?

1418
01:21:56,290 --> 01:21:58,040
About her face?

1419
01:21:59,206 --> 01:22:01,331
And that bastard...

1420
01:22:04,373 --> 01:22:06,831
...finally said it.

1421
01:22:08,915 --> 01:22:10,956
That your mom's face...

1422
01:22:13,540 --> 01:22:18,456
...was hideously ugly, like a monster.

1423
01:22:25,040 --> 01:22:27,373
That's when I found out everything.

1424
01:22:36,915 --> 01:22:37,916
Those bastards...

1425
01:22:39,956 --> 01:22:44,873
...no, those scumbags were mocking me.

1426
01:22:47,905 --> 01:22:49,545
Mocking me all along.

1427
01:23:08,540 --> 01:23:12,415
From a young age,
I was mocked and belittled...

1428
01:23:15,248 --> 01:23:18,331
...I worked so hard to break free from it.

1429
01:23:20,165 --> 01:23:21,206
But then...

1430
01:23:22,326 --> 01:23:24,576
...it just kept happening.

1431
01:23:24,925 --> 01:23:25,825
Over and over!

1432
01:23:31,425 --> 01:23:32,304
A monster...

1433
01:23:34,373 --> 01:23:35,373
Why?

1434
01:23:36,700 --> 01:23:41,367
You think I can't tell what's
beautiful and what's ugly?

1435
01:23:44,305 --> 01:23:49,305
People may secretly look down on me,
but why bow before me?

1436
01:23:51,374 --> 01:23:55,207
Because my engravings are beautiful.

1437
01:23:55,454 --> 01:23:56,625
So beautiful.

1438
01:23:58,705 --> 01:23:59,748
I know it.

1439
01:24:01,865 --> 01:24:04,625
Beautiful things are respected and admired.

1440
01:24:06,705 --> 01:24:09,425
Ugly things are scorned.

1441
01:24:12,377 --> 01:24:13,669
I know it all.

1442
01:24:13,969 --> 01:24:15,633
(Indistinct Chatter)

1443
01:24:21,117 --> 01:24:22,820
(Indistinct Chatter)

1444
01:24:23,425 --> 01:24:26,705
It was only then I started to see
things I hadn't noticed before.

1445
01:24:26,875 --> 01:24:28,617
(Indistinct Laughter)

1446
01:24:29,039 --> 01:24:29,945
Everything.

1447
01:24:31,790 --> 01:24:32,656
Everything.

1448
01:24:33,234 --> 01:24:35,265
(Indistinct Laughter and Chatter)

1449
01:24:40,417 --> 01:24:42,641
(Indistinct Laughter)

1450
01:24:45,974 --> 01:24:48,890
In the end, even your mother deceived me.

1451
01:24:49,023 --> 01:24:50,351
(Indistinct Chatter)

1452
01:24:50,545 --> 01:24:52,670
How little must she have thought of me?

1453
01:24:56,001 --> 01:25:00,209
She approached me just to ridicule me.

1454
01:25:06,189 --> 01:25:08,022
If I stayed with her...

1455
01:25:09,222 --> 01:25:12,389
...I felt I could never
escape the humiliation.

1456
01:25:15,398 --> 01:25:17,856
No matter how hard I struggled,
it didn't work.

1457
01:25:19,090 --> 01:25:20,537
I couldn't live with that woman.

1458
01:25:21,328 --> 01:25:26,117
(Liquid Pouring)

1459
01:25:26,345 --> 01:25:28,928
Even when she got into
a fight with Mr. Baek...

1460
01:25:29,928 --> 01:25:32,345
...why did she make things
so difficult for me?

1461
01:25:33,095 --> 01:25:37,261
I told her to stop,
but she kept doing it just to spite me.

1462
01:25:39,914 --> 01:25:41,680
(Water Dripping)

1463
01:25:44,065 --> 01:25:45,565
Please, just die.

1464
01:25:46,333 --> 01:25:49,333
Just die, die...

1465
01:25:50,428 --> 01:25:52,928
Someone, please kill her for me.

1466
01:25:53,146 --> 01:25:54,104
Kill her...

1467
01:25:54,929 --> 01:25:56,608
(Thud)

1468
01:25:56,609 --> 01:25:59,016
(Whimpering)

1469
01:25:59,428 --> 01:26:02,803
No matter how much I prayed...

1470
01:26:03,220 --> 01:26:06,053
...she never intended to leave me.

1471
01:26:06,772 --> 01:26:11,356
Even after being beaten,
she kept going back for more.

1472
01:26:22,303 --> 01:26:26,678
I never imagined I'd
be the one to kill her.

1473
01:26:29,970 --> 01:26:31,636
Never thought of it.

1474
01:26:35,011 --> 01:26:36,220
Never.

1475
01:26:41,625 --> 01:26:43,245
Did you go see the boss again?

1476
01:26:46,825 --> 01:26:47,624
Did you?

1477
01:26:50,785 --> 01:26:51,827
Did you?!

1478
01:26:52,728 --> 01:26:54,186
You know...

1479
01:26:54,802 --> 01:26:55,590
Why...

1480
01:26:58,545 --> 01:27:03,669
Why do you keep stirring up trouble?!

1481
01:27:03,670 --> 01:27:05,047
(Thud)

1482
01:27:05,406 --> 01:27:07,711
(Baby Crying)

1483
01:27:09,234 --> 01:27:10,120
(Gasps)

1484
01:27:10,121 --> 01:27:11,563
(Baby Crying)

1485
01:27:11,705 --> 01:27:14,904
What did I... what did I do wrong?

1486
01:27:14,905 --> 01:27:16,278
For God's sake!

1487
01:27:16,539 --> 01:27:18,367
(Baby Crying)

1488
01:27:18,508 --> 01:27:20,586
(Whimpering)

1489
01:27:20,865 --> 01:27:21,990
Honey.

1490
01:27:22,195 --> 01:27:23,414
(Baby Crying)

1491
01:27:23,505 --> 01:27:30,505
Please... just mind your own business!

1492
01:27:31,234 --> 01:27:32,969
(Baby Crying)

1493
01:27:33,353 --> 01:27:37,728
Like a little mouse...

1494
01:27:39,185 --> 01:27:45,310
...let's just live quietly...

1495
01:27:45,648 --> 01:27:48,547
(Sobbing)

1496
01:27:51,844 --> 01:27:53,710
(Whimpering)

1497
01:27:55,945 --> 01:27:57,651
Since I was a child...

1498
01:27:57,652 --> 01:27:58,578
(Gasps)

1499
01:27:59,665 --> 01:28:02,425
...people have always blamed me.

1500
01:28:02,516 --> 01:28:03,984
(Whimpering)

1501
01:28:05,105 --> 01:28:06,453
That I was the problem.

1502
01:28:06,586 --> 01:28:08,648
(Whimpering)

1503
01:28:09,227 --> 01:28:15,227
So I thought I had to live pretending
not to see or know anything.

1504
01:28:17,227 --> 01:28:22,352
For a while,
I really tried to live like that.

1505
01:28:22,742 --> 01:28:24,156
(Whimpering)

1506
01:28:24,909 --> 01:28:27,117
But you...

1507
01:28:27,118 --> 01:28:27,992
(Gasps)

1508
01:28:28,501 --> 01:28:30,792
You were kind to me -.

1509
01:28:30,793 --> 01:28:32,097
Stop it.

1510
01:28:34,117 --> 01:28:35,273
(Gasps)

1511
01:28:36,145 --> 01:28:38,068
You gave me courage.

1512
01:28:41,685 --> 01:28:42,989
Because of you.

1513
01:28:51,060 --> 01:28:52,145
You didn't just...

1514
01:28:53,785 --> 01:28:55,463
Just see me as ugly...

1515
01:28:55,464 --> 01:28:56,462
Dammit.

1516
01:28:56,463 --> 01:28:57,719
(Glass Shattering)

1517
01:28:57,720 --> 01:29:01,078
Shut up, you stupid bitch!

1518
01:29:01,229 --> 01:29:04,438
If you had any conscience...

1519
01:29:05,039 --> 01:29:06,951
(Baby Crying)

1520
01:29:06,952 --> 01:29:09,852
...you wouldn't dare say that, you bitch.

1521
01:29:10,195 --> 01:29:13,320
(Whimpering)

1522
01:29:13,914 --> 01:29:15,789
(Baby Crying)

1523
01:29:16,070 --> 01:29:16,991
(Scratching)

1524
01:29:16,992 --> 01:29:18,164
(Grunts)

1525
01:29:19,422 --> 01:29:21,273
(Groans)

1526
01:29:23,445 --> 01:29:26,297
(Baby Crying)

1527
01:29:38,109 --> 01:29:40,414
(Baby Crying)

1528
01:29:40,664 --> 01:29:41,859
(Grunts)

1529
01:29:41,969 --> 01:29:44,305
(Baby Crying)

1530
01:29:44,703 --> 01:29:45,835
(Gasps)

1531
01:29:45,836 --> 01:29:48,257
(Baby Crying)

1532
01:29:56,121 --> 01:29:57,387
(Gasps)

1533
01:30:00,609 --> 01:30:01,987
(Baby Crying)

1534
01:30:01,988 --> 01:30:03,095
(Shushing)

1535
01:30:03,539 --> 01:30:05,164
(Gasps)

1536
01:30:06,023 --> 01:30:08,641
(Baby Crying)

1537
01:30:09,961 --> 01:30:11,883
(Gasps)

1538
01:30:13,705 --> 01:30:14,985
No one will ever find out.

1539
01:30:17,425 --> 01:30:22,745
No... Nobody cares anyway.

1540
01:30:25,025 --> 01:30:25,926
Dong-hwan.

1541
01:30:26,344 --> 01:30:27,320
(Gasps)

1542
01:30:28,665 --> 01:30:30,705
With my own bare hands...

1543
01:30:32,545 --> 01:30:38,295
...I drove out the humiliation
that forced its way into my life.

1544
01:30:39,185 --> 01:30:40,690
Without anyone ever knowing.

1545
01:31:44,505 --> 01:31:45,365
Dong-hwan.

1546
01:31:48,138 --> 01:31:49,305
You get it, don't you?

1547
01:31:53,750 --> 01:31:54,882
(Gasps)

1548
01:31:55,389 --> 01:32:00,145
Honestly,
this might've all been for you too.

1549
01:32:01,987 --> 01:32:03,039
(Sniffles)

1550
01:32:03,985 --> 01:32:06,277
You need to understand that. Right?

1551
01:32:06,826 --> 01:32:07,951
Come here.

1552
01:32:08,476 --> 01:32:10,392
Son, come here.

1553
01:32:12,478 --> 01:32:16,437
I only wanted to pass
on good things to you.

1554
01:32:20,785 --> 01:32:22,865
You have to understand.

1555
01:32:23,427 --> 01:32:24,302
Come here.

1556
01:32:24,303 --> 01:32:25,628
I don't understand you.

1557
01:32:29,905 --> 01:32:30,925
I just can't.

1558
01:32:36,447 --> 01:32:40,072
If you don't,
then you're nothing but a parasite.

1559
01:32:41,425 --> 01:32:42,300
What?

1560
01:32:43,262 --> 01:32:47,512
A parasite feeding off everything
I've worked for my entire life.

1561
01:32:50,145 --> 01:32:51,237
You must understand.

1562
01:33:04,160 --> 01:33:05,952
You're a murderer.

1563
01:33:07,500 --> 01:33:08,180
(Thud)

1564
01:33:09,035 --> 01:33:13,577
No! Who's a murderer? No, dammit! Not me!

1565
01:33:13,705 --> 01:33:15,487
(Groans)

1566
01:33:15,825 --> 01:33:17,514
The statute of limitations has expired!

1567
01:33:18,236 --> 01:33:19,159
(Door Closes)

1568
01:33:19,160 --> 01:33:20,642
You think I don't know that?!

1569
01:33:21,041 --> 01:33:24,362
(Panting)

1570
01:33:24,625 --> 01:33:28,875
I'm a living miracle of Korea!

1571
01:33:29,190 --> 01:33:31,635
(Panting)

1572
01:33:32,305 --> 01:33:34,113
A man who sees the world
through his fingertips.

1573
01:33:35,330 --> 01:33:36,674
(Sighs)

1574
01:33:37,425 --> 01:33:39,008
A living miracle...

1575
01:33:40,185 --> 01:33:41,705
I'm not a murderer.

1576
01:33:42,291 --> 01:33:44,510
(Pants)

1577
01:33:47,145 --> 01:33:50,103
<i>The Last Remark.</i>

1578
01:33:54,823 --> 01:33:58,158
(Footstep)

1579
01:34:16,002 --> 01:34:17,143
(Chair Creaks)

1580
01:34:17,369 --> 01:34:18,244
(Thud)

1581
01:34:23,283 --> 01:34:24,627
(Sighs)

1582
01:34:26,785 --> 01:34:29,145
You admired your father so much...

1583
01:34:32,303 --> 01:34:35,261
...you sure about this?

1584
01:34:36,955 --> 01:34:38,088
(Gasps)

1585
01:34:38,865 --> 01:34:43,641
I deleted some unnecessary parts.

1586
01:34:45,243 --> 01:34:46,035
Pardon?

1587
01:34:46,745 --> 01:34:53,370
Please make sure
the documentary wraps up nicely.

1588
01:34:55,128 --> 01:34:55,987
(Scoffs)

1589
01:34:56,625 --> 01:34:58,666
You know, my father...

1590
01:35:00,825 --> 01:35:04,264
...he's a living miracle of Korea
for overcoming such difficult times.

1591
01:35:04,265 --> 01:35:05,413
So, please...

1592
01:35:09,505 --> 01:35:11,464
I'm counting on you.

1593
01:35:16,737 --> 01:35:17,924
(Scoffs)

1594
01:35:21,846 --> 01:35:22,893
(Scoffs)

1595
01:35:24,996 --> 01:35:25,934
You resemble him.

1596
01:35:28,825 --> 01:35:29,825
Sorry?

1597
01:35:30,918 --> 01:35:31,773
Your father.

1598
01:35:34,625 --> 01:35:36,425
You resemble him even more today.

1599
01:35:40,760 --> 01:35:42,112
(Sighs)

1600
01:35:42,665 --> 01:35:47,207
I spoke a bit more with
Baek Joo-sang yesterday.

1601
01:35:48,942 --> 01:35:52,484
All of these are my works.

1602
01:35:53,790 --> 01:35:56,290
They're art pieces.

1603
01:35:57,432 --> 01:35:58,479
(Sighs)

1604
01:36:01,985 --> 01:36:04,860
Why didn't you take
a photo of Jung Young-hee?

1605
01:36:06,985 --> 01:36:09,705
There is one.

1606
01:36:11,568 --> 01:36:19,360
I took ID photos of all new employees.

1607
01:36:20,158 --> 01:36:22,674
(Sobbing)

1608
01:36:25,643 --> 01:36:26,502
(Grunts)

1609
01:36:31,527 --> 01:36:34,693
Eun-sook, smile big!

1610
01:36:35,228 --> 01:36:38,305
Hold it up, a little higher.
Yeah, closer to the chest.

1611
01:36:38,485 --> 01:36:40,360
So pretty, that's it.

1612
01:36:40,585 --> 01:36:42,628
Okay, smile, one...

1613
01:36:42,629 --> 01:36:43,704
...two...

1614
01:36:43,705 --> 01:36:44,679
(Camera Shutter Click)

1615
01:36:44,680 --> 01:36:46,623
...Jung Young-hee three!

1616
01:36:46,624 --> 01:36:48,110
So pretty.

1617
01:36:48,610 --> 01:36:49,652
All done, go.

1618
01:36:50,568 --> 01:36:51,777
Next.

1619
01:37:01,065 --> 01:37:03,565
Hey, Jung Young-hee.

1620
01:37:03,566 --> 01:37:07,323
Why is your hair loose for an ID photo?

1621
01:37:07,745 --> 01:37:10,545
Tie it up so your face shows better.

1622
01:37:15,328 --> 01:37:17,411
Alright, here we go.

1623
01:37:19,105 --> 01:37:20,605
Smile.

1624
01:37:20,775 --> 01:37:21,983
Cheese.

1625
01:37:22,104 --> 01:37:23,082
(Camera Shutter Click)

1626
01:37:23,083 --> 01:37:24,337
One.

1627
01:37:24,817 --> 01:37:26,025
Two.

1628
01:37:26,195 --> 01:37:26,897
Three!

1629
01:37:27,201 --> 01:37:27,923
(Camera Shutter Click)

1630
01:37:27,924 --> 01:37:28,893
(Paper Rustle)

1631
01:37:29,002 --> 01:37:30,276
(Slides)

1632
01:37:32,895 --> 01:37:34,105
It's your mother's photo.

1633
01:37:37,558 --> 01:37:39,776
That is, if you're still interested.

1634
01:38:03,205 --> 01:38:05,151
(Paper Rustle)

1635
01:38:40,494 --> 01:38:41,518
(Sobbing)

1636
01:38:46,869 --> 01:38:48,260
(Sobbing)

1637
01:39:04,994 --> 01:39:06,408
(Sniffles)

1638
01:39:17,252 --> 01:39:19,026
(Sniffles)

1639
01:39:25,932 --> 01:39:27,854
(Sobbing)

